116
00:07:30,292 --> 00:07:31,667
[voice shaking] Please don't...

117
00:07:31,750 --> 00:07:32,792
kill me.

118
00:07:35,917 --> 00:07:37,917
[breathing heavily, grunting]

119
00:07:38,542 --> 00:07:40,042
Oh, don't worry.

120
00:07:40,833 --> 00:07:43,500
[screams, groans]

121
00:07:44,833 --> 00:07:46,333
I'm one of the good guys.

122
00:07:46,417 --> 00:07:48,250
♪ I'm just taking a Greyhound ♪

123
00:07:48,333 --> 00:07:49,375
[whines]

124
00:07:49,458 --> 00:07:50,875
♪ On the Hudson River Line ♪

125
00:07:50,958 --> 00:07:52,458
[man over radio] Negative.
Can we know get an...

126
00:07:52,542 --> 00:07:53,792
It's fucking Bullseye!

127
00:07:54,708 --> 00:07:56,667
It's Bullseye! It's-- [grunts]

128
00:08:00,375 --> 00:08:01,375
[chuckles]

129
00:08:01,958 --> 00:08:02,958
[whines]

130
00:08:03,042 --> 00:08:04,833
♪ 'Cause I'm in ♪

131
00:08:09,875 --> 00:08:12,083
♪ I'm in a New York ♪

132
00:08:12,167 --> 00:08:14,583
[ketchup bottle squirts]

133
00:08:14,667 --> 00:08:20,500
♪ State of mind ♪

134
00:08:20,583 --> 00:08:21,917
[doorbell dinging]

135
00:08:22,542 --> 00:08:26,458
♪ Yeah, yeah ♪

136
00:08:39,333 --> 00:08:41,417
[♪ theme music playing]

137
00:10:20,375 --> 00:10:22,375
[City Without Fear voice] It's me again.

138
00:10:22,458 --> 00:10:24,292
A cringe explosion in the East River?

139
00:10:24,375 --> 00:10:25,833
Don't worry about it!

140
00:10:25,917 --> 00:10:27,083
Floating dead bodies?

141
00:10:27,167 --> 00:10:28,750
Don't worry about it.

142
00:10:28,833 --> 00:10:32,500
All smoke and mirrors,
distracting you from the main event!

143
00:10:32,583 --> 00:10:34,417
-My charity boxing match...
-[bell dings]

144
00:10:34,500 --> 00:10:38,250
...that's raising money for a New York
Born Again revitalization project,

145
00:10:38,333 --> 00:10:39,792
that is really a shell corporation
for money laundering

146
00:10:39,875 --> 00:10:41,958
to offshore accounts
that make my friends grotesquely rich.

147
00:10:42,042 --> 00:10:43,167
[breathing heavily]

148
00:10:43,250 --> 00:10:47,083
I've been training hard at the gym
for you, New York.

149
00:10:47,167 --> 00:10:48,708
The money we will raise will go to

150
00:10:48,792 --> 00:10:49,792
arresting you without due process,

151
00:10:49,875 --> 00:10:51,000
seizing your property
for my personal gain,

152
00:10:51,083 --> 00:10:53,083
locking up your loved ones,
and so much more.

153
00:10:53,167 --> 00:10:55,625
Back to the gym, I go, because

154
00:10:55,708 --> 00:10:58,208
I love you, New York!

155
00:10:58,750 --> 00:11:01,167
[horns blaring distantly]

156
00:11:01,250 --> 00:11:04,083
[officer] We're getting split
by coordinates. Nothing to report.

157
00:11:05,750 --> 00:11:08,208
[Soledad] My name is Soledad Ayala.

158
00:11:08,292 --> 00:11:10,958
I am a nurse from Washington Heights.

159
00:11:11,042 --> 00:11:13,500
I was arrested by the Task Force,

160
00:11:13,583 --> 00:11:16,333
the same people who killed my husband.

161
00:11:17,292 --> 00:11:18,292
I am the missing.

162
00:11:19,583 --> 00:11:20,833
But I will not back down.

163
00:11:21,917 --> 00:11:22,917
I will stay...

164
00:11:23,625 --> 00:11:24,667
and fight.

165
00:11:25,542 --> 00:11:28,042
-[device beeps]
-[Karen] It's okay. Thank you.

166
00:11:28,125 --> 00:11:29,583
[Jack] It's time for me to go.

167
00:11:29,667 --> 00:11:31,125
I wish you'd reconsider.

168
00:11:31,208 --> 00:11:34,750
[chuckles] I have been
in a cage for... [sighs]

169
00:11:34,833 --> 00:11:36,750
...six months.

170
00:11:36,833 --> 00:11:40,042
I need to shower.
I need to burn these clothes. [sighs]

171
00:11:40,125 --> 00:11:41,542
I'm too old for this shit.

172
00:11:41,625 --> 00:11:44,292
Ah, it's a shame 'cause we could use
more people like you.

173
00:11:45,458 --> 00:11:46,458
Like me?

174
00:11:48,333 --> 00:11:49,792
You don't realize it, do you?

175
00:11:50,958 --> 00:11:52,250
You're not a hero.

176
00:11:53,250 --> 00:11:54,833
You're a symbol now.

177
00:11:54,917 --> 00:11:56,750
Hope for an entire city.

178
00:11:58,667 --> 00:11:59,667
It's true.

179
00:12:00,542 --> 00:12:02,250
I gave Karen an account number.

180
00:12:02,333 --> 00:12:03,917
Use whatever you need,

181
00:12:04,000 --> 00:12:05,083
whenever you need it.

182
00:12:05,167 --> 00:12:06,292
Thank you.

183
00:12:06,375 --> 00:12:07,750
Good luck, my friend.

184
00:12:08,833 --> 00:12:10,542
-Destroy them both.
-[chuckles]

185
00:12:14,958 --> 00:12:16,625
-[Angela] Hey.
-Hey.

186
00:12:16,708 --> 00:12:17,875
What you got there?

187
00:12:17,958 --> 00:12:20,583
Uh, SD card.
I'm supposed to get it to my source,

188
00:12:20,667 --> 00:12:21,833
but with the Task Force everywhere,

189
00:12:21,917 --> 00:12:23,417
-I'm too exposed.
-It's okay.

190
00:12:24,250 --> 00:12:25,500
Let me do it.

191
00:12:25,583 --> 00:12:28,625
-[chuckles] Absolutely not.
-Oh, come on.

192
00:12:29,542 --> 00:12:32,542
[whispering] No, come on, I just need
to do this for my aunt, please.

193
00:12:34,167 --> 00:12:36,667
[sighs] No way. It's too dangerous.

194
00:12:37,625 --> 00:12:38,625
So what?

195
00:12:38,708 --> 00:12:40,042
I stole their truck.

196
00:12:40,125 --> 00:12:42,833
[whispering] They're probably already
looking for me. [chuckles softly]

197
00:12:42,917 --> 00:12:44,792
[♪ tense music playing]

198
00:12:48,083 --> 00:12:49,333
[Karen sighs]

199
00:12:53,667 --> 00:12:54,750
Thank you.

200
00:12:54,833 --> 00:12:55,958
Be careful.

201
00:13:05,417 --> 00:13:06,417
[inhales sharply]

202
00:13:08,875 --> 00:13:09,917
[sighs]

203
00:13:10,875 --> 00:13:12,333
[soft clinking]

204
00:13:15,583 --> 00:13:17,917
Do you understand the responsibility
that comes with this?

205
00:13:19,542 --> 00:13:20,583
Yeah,

206
00:13:20,667 --> 00:13:21,708
I do.

207
00:13:22,833 --> 00:13:23,958
Are you ready?

208
00:13:25,292 --> 00:13:26,292
[chuckles]

209
00:13:27,250 --> 00:13:28,250
Were you?

210
00:13:28,750 --> 00:13:30,458
[rumbling]

211
00:13:30,542 --> 00:13:32,500
-[heart thumping]
-[heavy breathing]

212
00:13:33,458 --> 00:13:34,875
[whispering] Everybody, stay still.

213
00:13:43,333 --> 00:13:45,708
-[thumping continues]
-[♪ tense music playing]

214
00:13:50,292 --> 00:13:51,417
[creaking]

215
00:13:52,875 --> 00:13:54,833
[man yells, grunts]

216
00:13:56,458 --> 00:13:58,917
[gasps] My name is Christofi Savva.

217
00:13:59,000 --> 00:14:00,458
I'm here to help. [gasps]

218
00:14:00,542 --> 00:14:02,958
I was the First Mate on the Northern Star.

219
00:14:04,042 --> 00:14:05,583
[breathes heavily]

220
00:14:13,250 --> 00:14:14,250
[kisses]

221
00:14:14,875 --> 00:14:17,083
That's one way to deal with the Governor.

222
00:14:18,958 --> 00:14:20,250
It's for the journey,

223
00:14:20,333 --> 00:14:21,333
not the meeting.

224
00:14:21,417 --> 00:14:23,542
Marge and I have a rapport.

225
00:14:26,417 --> 00:14:28,375
And I appreciate you talkin' to her.

226
00:14:30,125 --> 00:14:31,542
I know what you're doing.

227
00:14:32,833 --> 00:14:34,208
Arranging this

228
00:14:34,292 --> 00:14:36,583
trip to Albany just before the fight.

229
00:14:38,833 --> 00:14:40,125
I don't like it...

230
00:14:41,458 --> 00:14:43,708
when you send me away and shut me out.

231
00:14:45,625 --> 00:14:47,000
This is not that.

232
00:14:47,083 --> 00:14:48,667
It's a public place.

233
00:14:50,792 --> 00:14:52,917
Too much could go wrong.

234
00:14:55,458 --> 00:14:57,167
We're a matched set.

235
00:14:57,708 --> 00:14:59,292
I should be there tonight.

236
00:15:03,250 --> 00:15:04,875
I'll call you when it's over.

237
00:15:06,583 --> 00:15:08,250
[inhales deeply]

238
00:15:13,417 --> 00:15:16,208
[♪ eerie music playing]

239
00:15:34,500 --> 00:15:35,583
Good luck.

240
00:15:43,292 --> 00:15:46,458
[door opens, shuts]

241
00:15:47,333 --> 00:15:49,708
[Christofi] You were captured
only for helping me.

242
00:15:52,583 --> 00:15:54,625
I would like to return that kindness.

243
00:15:57,083 --> 00:15:59,500
What can you tell us
about the Northern Star?

244
00:16:01,000 --> 00:16:02,083
Everything.

245
00:16:03,042 --> 00:16:05,250
The illegal weapons, the fake documents...

246
00:16:08,958 --> 00:16:11,542
Can you connect any of it to Fisk?

247
00:16:15,083 --> 00:16:16,375
We were protected.

248
00:16:17,042 --> 00:16:19,875
All the paperwork was signed off by...

249
00:16:21,125 --> 00:16:22,667
Vasillias tou Enklimatos.

250
00:16:24,208 --> 00:16:25,625
The Kingpin.

251
00:16:32,375 --> 00:16:34,625
Well, we need an attorney
to take his statement.

252
00:16:36,542 --> 00:16:38,250
-[sighs] Kirsten...
-Yeah, yeah.

253
00:16:38,333 --> 00:16:39,667
Well, it's too dangerous
to bring Christofi to her,

254
00:16:39,750 --> 00:16:41,042
so she'll have to come to us.

255
00:16:41,125 --> 00:16:43,542
Won't be too hard. All the Task Force
will be at the fight tonight.

256
00:16:43,625 --> 00:16:44,875
Yeah, yeah.

257
00:16:44,958 --> 00:16:46,375
At Fogwell's.

258
00:16:49,542 --> 00:16:51,667
Some of the last memories
of my father are in that gym.

259
00:16:52,542 --> 00:16:54,667
[sighs] Now, it's crawling
with Task Force.

260
00:16:55,500 --> 00:16:56,833
Yeah, he wants me there.

261
00:16:57,333 --> 00:17:00,042
-[inhales deeply]
-Or...

262
00:17:00,917 --> 00:17:02,083
Not just me.

263
00:17:02,167 --> 00:17:03,208
The whole fight--

264
00:17:03,292 --> 00:17:04,542
He's setting a trap for Bullseye.

265
00:17:05,292 --> 00:17:06,542
[sighs] Oh, fuck.

266
00:17:08,333 --> 00:17:10,083
-[grunts] I'm gonna find Bullseye.
-Mm-hmm.

267
00:17:10,167 --> 00:17:12,042
-You just connect Kirsten and Christofi.
-Christofi.

268
00:17:12,125 --> 00:17:13,292
Yep. [sighs]

269
00:17:13,375 --> 00:17:15,167
-All right. Be careful.
-You, too.

270
00:17:18,125 --> 00:17:19,250
I love you.

271
00:17:22,167 --> 00:17:23,375
I love you, too.

272
00:17:27,458 --> 00:17:29,125
[reporter] I'm here outside Fogwell's Gym,

273
00:17:29,208 --> 00:17:33,542
a part of Mayor Fisk's Born Again
revitalization project,

274
00:17:33,625 --> 00:17:35,958
and host to tonight's benefit boxing match

275
00:17:36,042 --> 00:17:37,917
between the Mayor and heavyweight

276
00:17:38,000 --> 00:17:39,917
Mike "the Matterhorn" Melendez.

277
00:17:40,000 --> 00:17:42,292
Due to the recent spate
of vigilante violence,

278
00:17:42,375 --> 00:17:43,917
I'm told security will be tight,

279
00:17:44,000 --> 00:17:46,167
-with increased Task Force to--
-[shatters]

280
00:17:47,333 --> 00:17:48,625
[Kirsten] No, I don't understand.

281
00:17:48,708 --> 00:17:51,542
I was under the impression
that that account was paid in full.

282
00:17:52,708 --> 00:17:54,625
[shouting] Down on the fucking ground now!

283
00:17:54,708 --> 00:17:57,458
Down on the fucking ground!
Out of your fucking chairs! Down!

284
00:17:57,542 --> 00:17:59,250
-On the fucking ground! Down!
-[Kirsten] Hey! Hey!

285
00:17:59,333 --> 00:18:02,958
You assholes better have a warrant, or
I'm gonna bury you under so many lawsuits

286
00:18:03,042 --> 00:18:06,792
that your grandchildren's grandchildren
will still be paying your legal bills.

287
00:18:06,875 --> 00:18:08,042
-Safer Streets.
-[objects clattering]

288
00:18:08,125 --> 00:18:11,250
-I don't need a warrant or probable cause.
-We won't even need to knock.

289
00:18:12,000 --> 00:18:13,000
You again?

290
00:18:14,125 --> 00:18:15,750
-[Powell] Where's your client?
-[Kirsten] Which one?

291
00:18:15,833 --> 00:18:18,167
[Powell] Terrorist fugitive Jack Duquesne,
also known as Swordsman.

292
00:18:18,250 --> 00:18:21,042
-Allegedly.
-A court of law found him guilty.

293
00:18:21,667 --> 00:18:22,833
That was no court.

294
00:18:23,333 --> 00:18:25,167
Whatever.
I'm not gonna fucking ask you again.

295
00:18:25,250 --> 00:18:26,625
Do you see him here? Anywhere?

296
00:18:26,708 --> 00:18:30,167
Maybe he's hiding under a pile of files
or that wall made of glass.

297
00:18:30,250 --> 00:18:31,292
Nothing, sir.

298
00:18:32,750 --> 00:18:34,000
You hear from him, you turn him in.

299
00:18:34,083 --> 00:18:35,875
Attorney-client privilege still applies.

300
00:18:35,958 --> 00:18:38,667
I don't give a fuck about your
attorney-client whatever the fuck.

301
00:18:38,750 --> 00:18:40,750
He was part of a terrorist attack
that killed 25 men

302
00:18:40,833 --> 00:18:42,333
-on board that ship.
-Bullshit.

303
00:18:42,917 --> 00:18:44,125
Talk like that will get you hurt someday.

304
00:18:44,208 --> 00:18:46,167
Talk like that is how I do my fucking job.

305
00:18:48,875 --> 00:18:51,542
You tell Matt Murdock we said hello. Okay?

306
00:18:55,667 --> 00:18:56,750
See you around, Counselor!

307
00:18:58,250 --> 00:18:59,250
[clatters]

308
00:19:02,583 --> 00:19:04,625
[Fisk] First, Bullseye and now this.

309
00:19:04,708 --> 00:19:05,958
And how many escaped?

310
00:19:06,042 --> 00:19:07,417
Nineteen in total.

311
00:19:07,875 --> 00:19:09,750
[sighs] I've had enough!

312
00:19:10,750 --> 00:19:13,333
There's leaks in Red Hook,
leaks in City Hall!

313
00:19:13,417 --> 00:19:14,792
You need to find them, Buck!

314
00:19:14,875 --> 00:19:16,208
Plug them!

315
00:19:16,292 --> 00:19:17,375
Every one!

316
00:19:18,750 --> 00:19:20,500
-How much you wanna know?
-Enough to know what's--

317
00:19:20,583 --> 00:19:21,750
[Charles] You know what I wanna know?

318
00:19:22,375 --> 00:19:23,625
Why... [munching]

319
00:19:23,708 --> 00:19:25,708
...is wombat shit cube-shaped?

320
00:19:26,500 --> 00:19:28,167
I mean, it's the strangest thing
I've ever seen.

321
00:19:29,042 --> 00:19:31,500
Apparently, they like to
stack it into, like,

322
00:19:31,583 --> 00:19:35,458
little walls that mark
their territory. [laughs]

323
00:19:35,542 --> 00:19:36,625
Isn't that weird?

324
00:19:36,708 --> 00:19:39,875
Little Lego walls of wombat shit

325
00:19:39,958 --> 00:19:41,125
to get the bitches.

326
00:19:41,208 --> 00:19:42,458
They literally shit bricks.

327
00:19:43,917 --> 00:19:47,208
Charles, you are not on my agenda.

328
00:19:47,292 --> 00:19:50,250
I have another awesome
existential question.

329
00:19:51,125 --> 00:19:53,375
Why is my non-cube shitting ass

330
00:19:53,458 --> 00:19:55,708
sitting on a pile of HK 416s

331
00:19:55,792 --> 00:19:59,417
and rocket launchers,
and other assorted weapons, when this,

332
00:19:59,500 --> 00:20:02,583
all of this, is not supposed to be
in a warehouse in Brooklyn.

333
00:20:02,667 --> 00:20:06,292
It's supposed to be on its way to
Guinea-Bissau to win the hearts and minds.

334
00:20:06,375 --> 00:20:08,708
Because Daredevil knows it's in New York.

335
00:20:09,417 --> 00:20:10,542
[Charles] People need these arms.

336
00:20:11,083 --> 00:20:12,750
Shots must be fired.

337
00:20:13,667 --> 00:20:15,750
If you put these on another boat,

338
00:20:15,833 --> 00:20:18,750
we'll have the Northern Star
all over again, or worse.

339
00:20:18,833 --> 00:20:22,125
And I don't need my city
turning on me. Not now.

340
00:20:22,208 --> 00:20:24,375
Your city. [laughs]

341
00:20:24,458 --> 00:20:26,167
-That's rich.
-Do not mock me!

342
00:20:26,250 --> 00:20:28,667
It is a big world out there, sailor.

343
00:20:28,750 --> 00:20:33,500
With big wars and much, much bigger stakes
than one elected official.

344
00:20:33,583 --> 00:20:35,958
Official who gave you access
to an American free port.

345
00:20:36,042 --> 00:20:38,458
And on behalf of the agency,
we appreciate your service.

346
00:20:38,542 --> 00:20:41,833
A service, I might remind you,
which is yet to be rendered.

347
00:20:42,458 --> 00:20:44,542
I will honor our arrangement.

348
00:20:45,208 --> 00:20:46,333
Well, that's great.

349
00:20:46,417 --> 00:20:48,708
I mean, the question kind of becomes
"Can you?" Right?

350
00:20:48,792 --> 00:20:52,500
I mean, you've been rocking and rolling
with all your big cat friends.

351
00:20:52,583 --> 00:20:55,917
And then Uncle Sam shows up,
and your facility, the...

352
00:20:56,000 --> 00:21:00,167
the golden fucking goose is cooked
because this place is compromised.

353
00:21:00,250 --> 00:21:03,375
And your Governor is threatening
to revoke its charter.

354
00:21:03,458 --> 00:21:05,167
You are overreaching.

355
00:21:05,250 --> 00:21:06,792
[Charles] From where I'm sitting,

356
00:21:06,875 --> 00:21:08,583
it seems to me you're having a--

357
00:21:08,667 --> 00:21:12,375
[grunts] Just a very difficult time
controlling...

358
00:21:13,083 --> 00:21:16,083
your very, very small piece of the world.

359
00:21:16,167 --> 00:21:17,708
I am not your employee!

360
00:21:18,625 --> 00:21:20,000
[breathes deeply]

361
00:21:21,583 --> 00:21:22,667
I never said you were.

362
00:21:23,458 --> 00:21:26,792
Partners, Wilson--
Come on! We're partners.

363
00:21:26,875 --> 00:21:28,958
Hey, I don't respond well to threats.

364
00:21:29,042 --> 00:21:30,333
[chuckling] That's not a threat.

365
00:21:32,417 --> 00:21:34,042
Look, neither of us ever walk in anywhere

366
00:21:34,125 --> 00:21:36,458
without knowing how we're gonna get out.

367
00:21:36,542 --> 00:21:39,208
[chuckles] It's adorable,
but you can put your hands down.

368
00:21:40,208 --> 00:21:41,292
You're right.

369
00:21:41,917 --> 00:21:44,458
-[officers grunt]
-[bodies thudding]

370
00:21:46,375 --> 00:21:49,625
[Fisk] Your shipment will be delivered
when the time is right.

371
00:21:50,167 --> 00:21:52,667
I would ask that you practice patience!

372
00:21:56,708 --> 00:21:58,583
Next time you wanna see me, call.

373
00:22:00,292 --> 00:22:01,292
It's courteous.

374
00:22:08,458 --> 00:22:11,083
-[door shuts]
-Shit.

375
00:22:12,167 --> 00:22:13,708
This was retaliation,

376
00:22:13,792 --> 00:22:16,042
and then our accounts
are mysteriously frozen.

377
00:22:16,125 --> 00:22:17,417
It's not a coincidence.

378
00:22:17,500 --> 00:22:18,917
I wouldn't be here if it wasn't important.

379
00:22:19,000 --> 00:22:20,125
Yeah. Well, the last time I helped you,

380
00:22:20,208 --> 00:22:22,333
I ended up as an accessory
to a terrorist attack.

381
00:22:22,417 --> 00:22:25,167
Well, and Fisk sunk that ship.
Not Daredevil.

382
00:22:30,250 --> 00:22:31,333
Where's Matt?

383
00:22:31,875 --> 00:22:32,875
Karen?

384
00:22:36,042 --> 00:22:38,833
[sighs] Can't answer that...

385
00:22:39,792 --> 00:22:40,833
but he's safe.

386
00:22:43,583 --> 00:22:44,625
Okay.

387
00:22:46,708 --> 00:22:48,292
You think you know people...

388
00:22:58,208 --> 00:22:59,208
Here.

389
00:23:01,375 --> 00:23:02,417
Thanks.

390
00:23:06,875 --> 00:23:08,125
You do, you know.

391
00:23:16,125 --> 00:23:17,583
All right. [sighs]

392
00:23:20,500 --> 00:23:23,708
What do you need? And how much
is it gonna screw with my life?

393
00:23:25,500 --> 00:23:26,667
[chuckles softly]

394
00:23:28,292 --> 00:23:30,708
[Governor] To be honest,
I was expecting the call.

395
00:23:30,792 --> 00:23:32,833
I just wasn't expecting it from you.

396
00:23:33,667 --> 00:23:36,458
It's not often I'm surprised. [sighs]

397
00:23:37,542 --> 00:23:40,583
[Vanessa] You and I speak
a more similar language than my husband.

398
00:23:40,667 --> 00:23:42,375
[Governor] The Mayor, I understand.

399
00:23:43,167 --> 00:23:45,500
It's you, that's the mystery to me.

400
00:23:46,167 --> 00:23:49,417
Now, he... he's like the White Bull,
crashing through everything.

401
00:23:50,083 --> 00:23:51,458
Does that make you Europa?

402
00:23:51,542 --> 00:23:54,375
Oh. I'm no victim.

403
00:23:54,458 --> 00:23:56,042
I'm not entirely sure she was either.

404
00:23:57,125 --> 00:24:01,125
[breathes deeply] We can be candid
with each other, right?

405
00:24:01,208 --> 00:24:02,792
Of course, that's why I'm here.

406
00:24:04,417 --> 00:24:06,708
I don't like the way your husband
wields his power.

407
00:24:07,458 --> 00:24:08,792
I don't trust it,

408
00:24:08,875 --> 00:24:10,417
and it makes me nervous.

409
00:24:11,208 --> 00:24:12,958
I don't see Safer Streets,

410
00:24:13,500 --> 00:24:15,417
a thriving economy, and...

411
00:24:15,500 --> 00:24:17,792
neighborhood revitalization as problems.

412
00:24:18,417 --> 00:24:19,750
"New York Born Again."

413
00:24:20,500 --> 00:24:23,042
-A bit grandiose, don't you think?
-[both chuckle]

414
00:24:23,125 --> 00:24:26,417
My husband has big plans
for the city he loves.

415
00:24:28,583 --> 00:24:30,917
It'd be a shame if New York's progress

416
00:24:31,750 --> 00:24:35,333
was halted because of
unfortunate decisions.

417
00:24:36,333 --> 00:24:38,250
I said the Mayor gives me pause.

418
00:24:38,333 --> 00:24:39,500
You don't.

419
00:24:39,583 --> 00:24:43,167
The city shuts down businesses,
you unload them to Cooper and others,

420
00:24:43,250 --> 00:24:45,917
laying down the infrastructure
for long-term growth.

421
00:24:46,000 --> 00:24:47,292
It's shrewd...

422
00:24:48,417 --> 00:24:49,792
and ruthless.

423
00:24:49,875 --> 00:24:51,542
And I mean that as a compliment.

424
00:24:52,125 --> 00:24:53,542
I take it as one.

425
00:24:54,458 --> 00:24:55,542
Thank you.

426
00:24:56,167 --> 00:24:59,583
You could have done all of this
on your own.

427
00:25:00,417 --> 00:25:04,000
And yet, you chose to do it with Wilson.

428
00:25:05,125 --> 00:25:06,125
Why?

429
00:25:11,333 --> 00:25:12,750
I never thought it'd be him.

430
00:25:12,833 --> 00:25:14,458
[♪ eerie music playing]

431
00:25:15,750 --> 00:25:16,750
And then it was.

432
00:25:18,875 --> 00:25:21,083
And now I can't imagine it...

433
00:25:23,833 --> 00:25:25,083
being any other way.

434
00:25:27,958 --> 00:25:30,750
Can you temper his darker impulses?

435
00:25:32,958 --> 00:25:35,917
You want guarantees that I can't give you,

436
00:25:36,000 --> 00:25:37,667
but I can give you this...

437
00:25:38,417 --> 00:25:41,250
my husband loves New York,
and I love my husband.

438
00:25:42,833 --> 00:25:45,458
And I know how to bring out
the very best in him.

439
00:25:48,083 --> 00:25:50,125
Honestly, I... I couldn't sleep at night

440
00:25:50,208 --> 00:25:51,625
backing Mayor Fisk.

441
00:25:56,208 --> 00:25:59,417
But I can back Mayor and Mrs. Fisk.

442
00:26:02,125 --> 00:26:03,250
Thank you.

443
00:26:07,417 --> 00:26:08,792
-Thank you.
-Okay.

444
00:26:09,375 --> 00:26:12,000
Uh, we ran out of guac, bro,
but shit's still gonna be bussin'.

445
00:26:12,083 --> 00:26:14,333
[♪ hip-hop song playing
over speaker]

446
00:26:14,417 --> 00:26:17,292
Uh, welcome to Arriba Arepas.

447
00:26:17,375 --> 00:26:18,417
What do you want?

448
00:26:18,500 --> 00:26:20,333
Una arepa paisa, por favor.

449
00:26:22,167 --> 00:26:23,958
Oh, my gosh. A leprechaun.

450
00:26:24,042 --> 00:26:26,417
-Did you lose your pot of gold?
-Just shut the fuck up, Javi.

451
00:26:28,458 --> 00:26:30,208
I need you to do something for me.

452
00:26:31,208 --> 00:26:32,292
Fuck is this?

453
00:26:33,917 --> 00:26:35,875
I need you not to screw it up.

454
00:26:36,417 --> 00:26:38,167
Chill, I got you.

455
00:26:38,833 --> 00:26:40,625
I will seriously beat your ass.

456
00:26:40,708 --> 00:26:42,375
Ay, ay!

457
00:26:42,458 --> 00:26:43,625
You don't want that arepa?

458
00:26:44,417 --> 00:26:45,458
I... I guess not.

459
00:26:47,208 --> 00:26:49,375
Yeah, I'm not taking customers right now.
Give me one second.

460
00:26:50,542 --> 00:26:51,667
[doorbell dinging]

461
00:27:01,292 --> 00:27:02,458
[squeaks]

462
00:27:04,417 --> 00:27:05,875
All right, wrap it up! Let's go.

463
00:27:05,958 --> 00:27:06,958
Get lost!

464
00:27:08,125 --> 00:27:09,417
[officer] CSI's not done.

465
00:27:09,500 --> 00:27:12,125
Vigilante crimes. Task Force jurisdiction.

466
00:27:12,208 --> 00:27:13,208
What, are you pulling rank?

467
00:27:13,292 --> 00:27:14,292
[Matt] Let's go!

468
00:27:14,875 --> 00:27:16,333
Want me to call my friends?

469
00:27:18,667 --> 00:27:20,708
[officer] Hate these Task Force pricks.

470
00:27:20,792 --> 00:27:22,208
-[door opens]
-[doorbell dinging]

471
00:27:25,208 --> 00:27:26,458
-[door closes]
-[doorbell dinging]

472
00:27:30,250 --> 00:27:32,417
[♪ eerie music playing]

473
00:27:33,500 --> 00:27:34,667
[Matt] Jesus Christ.

474
00:27:41,667 --> 00:27:42,708
[sniffs]

475
00:27:49,333 --> 00:27:51,000
[squeaks]

476
00:27:51,750 --> 00:27:52,750
[sniffs]

477
00:27:53,583 --> 00:27:54,875
[grunts softly]

478
00:28:11,250 --> 00:28:12,458
[chuckles]

479
00:28:12,542 --> 00:28:13,750
[bell tolling]

480
00:28:19,542 --> 00:28:21,375
[♪ somber choir music playing]

481
00:28:26,458 --> 00:28:27,958
[bell tolling]

482
00:28:29,167 --> 00:28:30,167
[sighs softly]

483
00:28:52,125 --> 00:28:53,417
[shuddering breaths]

484
00:28:59,875 --> 00:29:00,958
[grunts softly]

485
00:29:10,625 --> 00:29:11,750
"Saint Lucia,

486
00:29:11,833 --> 00:29:13,750
"your beautiful name signifies light.

487
00:29:14,500 --> 00:29:17,250
"By the light of the faith
that God bestowed upon you...

488
00:29:17,833 --> 00:29:22,417
"increase and preserve this light
in my soul so that I may avoid evil,

489
00:29:22,500 --> 00:29:24,917
"be zealous in the performance
of good works...

490
00:29:25,875 --> 00:29:29,292
"And abhor nothing so much
as the darkness of evil and sin.

491
00:29:30,625 --> 00:29:31,625
"Amen."

492
00:29:32,750 --> 00:29:34,167
[seminarian] Haven't heard
that one in a long time.

493
00:29:37,458 --> 00:29:38,458
I, uh...

494
00:29:39,042 --> 00:29:40,375
I knew a boy.

495
00:29:40,458 --> 00:29:42,417
Uh, he was blind.

496
00:29:43,083 --> 00:29:45,583
Saint Lucia got him through
some tough times.

497
00:29:47,625 --> 00:29:49,000
You seem troubled, officer.

498
00:29:51,542 --> 00:29:53,542
Actually, I... I, uh,
grew up in this church.

499
00:29:55,250 --> 00:29:56,333
Haven't been back in a minute.

500
00:29:57,167 --> 00:29:58,667
[seminarian] Tell me, what--
What brings you back?

501
00:30:05,875 --> 00:30:08,125
I found that at a murder scene today.

502
00:30:10,333 --> 00:30:12,292
These tokens are available
to all our parishioners.

503
00:30:12,375 --> 00:30:13,875
So I couldn't possibly know who left this.

504
00:30:16,625 --> 00:30:18,292
[heart thumping]

505
00:30:20,000 --> 00:30:21,458
Tell me who you think...

506
00:30:22,292 --> 00:30:23,292
left it.

507
00:30:25,542 --> 00:30:27,833
[breathes deeply]

508
00:30:29,167 --> 00:30:30,208
There was a man.

509
00:30:31,208 --> 00:30:33,083
He came looking for a nun
who used to be assigned here.

510
00:30:33,917 --> 00:30:34,917
This man...

511
00:30:35,583 --> 00:30:37,125
uh, what did he want?

512
00:30:37,833 --> 00:30:39,333
He came looking for, um...

513
00:30:40,292 --> 00:30:41,792
I-- I don't know.

514
00:30:42,542 --> 00:30:44,375
Counsel. Penance.

515
00:30:44,458 --> 00:30:45,458
I told him

516
00:30:45,542 --> 00:30:48,125
I wasn't a priest yet--
He held a knife on me.

517
00:30:48,708 --> 00:30:49,708
And what did he say?

518
00:30:52,333 --> 00:30:53,625
Listen to me...

519
00:30:54,750 --> 00:30:55,750
This man...

520
00:30:57,208 --> 00:30:58,583
is a killer.

521
00:30:58,667 --> 00:31:01,458
Even so, I can't turn someone over
to the police.

522
00:31:02,333 --> 00:31:03,917
His judgment is not for us to say.

523
00:31:04,000 --> 00:31:06,583
Yeah, I'm not gonna debate with you
whether or not he deserves grace...

524
00:31:07,583 --> 00:31:09,000
but I do need to find him,

525
00:31:09,083 --> 00:31:10,625
or others will die.

526
00:31:13,583 --> 00:31:14,833
What will you do...

527
00:31:16,000 --> 00:31:17,125
when you find him?

528
00:31:20,000 --> 00:31:21,000
I won't kill him.

529
00:31:26,417 --> 00:31:29,000
He told me he wakes every morning
to the sound of the church bells.

530
00:31:29,625 --> 00:31:31,875
And he watches me open the doors
for morning mass.

531
00:31:32,917 --> 00:31:34,208
Watches from where?

532
00:31:35,000 --> 00:31:36,375
His window.

533
00:31:36,458 --> 00:31:38,792
-[bell tolling]
-[indistinct chatter]

534
00:31:41,458 --> 00:31:43,000
[horn honking]

535
00:31:46,292 --> 00:31:47,333
[Dex] Let me help you with that.

536
00:31:50,625 --> 00:31:51,708
See you tomorrow.

537
00:31:52,292 --> 00:31:54,083
Such a nice boy.

538
00:31:55,958 --> 00:31:57,000
[coin clinks]

539
00:31:58,125 --> 00:31:59,458
[coins jingling]

540
00:31:59,542 --> 00:32:01,750
[truck beeping]

541
00:32:04,292 --> 00:32:05,292
[switch clicks]

542
00:32:13,208 --> 00:32:15,083
[♪ soft music playing over CD player]

543
00:32:18,042 --> 00:32:19,167
[♪ music stops]

544
00:32:20,000 --> 00:32:21,500
-[Dex grunts]
-[CD whooshing]

545
00:32:22,417 --> 00:32:23,417
[Daredevil yells]

546
00:32:24,583 --> 00:32:26,833
[both grunting]

547
00:32:28,583 --> 00:32:29,917
[both grunting]

548
00:32:37,417 --> 00:32:38,667
[both yell]

549
00:32:39,500 --> 00:32:42,125
-[grunts]
-[groans, breathes heavily]

550
00:32:45,667 --> 00:32:46,917
[Dex grunts]

551
00:32:50,000 --> 00:32:52,458
-[Daredevil yells]
-[Dex grunts]

552
00:32:52,542 --> 00:32:54,000
I'm on your side.

553
00:32:54,083 --> 00:32:55,583
[both grunting]

554
00:32:59,500 --> 00:33:01,792
[screams] What are you doing to my Tony?

555
00:33:03,375 --> 00:33:04,625
[breathing heavily]

556
00:33:07,292 --> 00:33:08,958
-[Mrs. Smithers screams]
-[Daredevil groans]

557
00:33:09,042 --> 00:33:10,333
[Dex grunts]

558
00:33:10,417 --> 00:33:11,417
Stop!

559
00:33:11,500 --> 00:33:12,625
-One good deed!
-[grunts]

560
00:33:12,708 --> 00:33:14,875
One good deed!

561
00:33:14,958 --> 00:33:16,208
Put the gun down!

562
00:33:16,292 --> 00:33:17,708
What I did--

563
00:33:17,792 --> 00:33:20,833
-What that woman had me do...
-[Daredevil] No, no, no, no, no.

564
00:33:20,917 --> 00:33:22,333
-...to your friend...
-Don't you bring him up!

565
00:33:22,917 --> 00:33:24,583
Don't you dare bring him up!
Not like this!

566
00:33:24,667 --> 00:33:26,000
But I had to get out.

567
00:33:26,500 --> 00:33:28,042
I had to get my mind back.

568
00:33:29,042 --> 00:33:30,125
And one good deed,

569
00:33:31,375 --> 00:33:32,667
it levels the scales again.

570
00:33:32,750 --> 00:33:35,750
Oh! Uh... [chuckling]

571
00:33:35,833 --> 00:33:37,708
-All right. Okay.
-[Mrs. Smithers] No!

572
00:33:37,792 --> 00:33:38,833
What is the, uh--

573
00:33:38,917 --> 00:33:40,917
What is this, uh, one good deed?

574
00:33:41,000 --> 00:33:42,375
What is it you wanna do?

575
00:33:42,458 --> 00:33:44,250
[panting] What you wouldn't do.

576
00:33:45,500 --> 00:33:46,750
What you won't do.

577
00:33:47,458 --> 00:33:50,167
[sighs] Fisk. [exhales]

578
00:33:50,250 --> 00:33:51,292
I can't...

579
00:33:51,375 --> 00:33:53,500
I can't let you make a martyr out of him.

580
00:33:54,625 --> 00:33:56,083
I'm gonna make things right.

581
00:33:57,542 --> 00:33:58,542
I'm gonna help you.

582
00:33:58,625 --> 00:34:00,750
Please. Look, just calm down.

583
00:34:02,458 --> 00:34:03,583
I am calm.

584
00:34:03,667 --> 00:34:04,875
-[Daredevil grunts]
-[Dex grunts]

585
00:34:07,625 --> 00:34:09,000
[meows]

586
00:34:10,000 --> 00:34:12,083
-[Mrs. Smithers speaking Polish]
-[grunting]

587
00:34:14,875 --> 00:34:16,417
[scooter engine revving]

588
00:34:16,500 --> 00:34:18,000
[Daredevil grunting]

589
00:34:20,667 --> 00:34:21,958
-[Dex grunts]
-[man grunting]

590
00:34:22,042 --> 00:34:23,208
[tires screech]

591
00:34:24,542 --> 00:34:25,833
[grunts]

592
00:34:25,917 --> 00:34:27,167
[engine accelerating]

593
00:34:27,958 --> 00:34:29,292
[panting]

594
00:34:31,833 --> 00:34:34,167
[Christofi in English] My name
is Christofi Savva.

595
00:34:34,750 --> 00:34:37,417
I was the First Mate on the Northern Star.

596
00:34:38,042 --> 00:34:41,125
My Captain, Achilleo Kyriacou,

597
00:34:41,208 --> 00:34:42,625
scuttled the ship.

598
00:34:42,708 --> 00:34:45,958
We were under orders to sink the ship

599
00:34:46,042 --> 00:34:47,458
if it was ever boarded.

600
00:34:48,583 --> 00:34:50,000
Why was that?

601
00:34:51,417 --> 00:34:54,375
Because the Northern Star
was carrying weapons,

602
00:34:54,458 --> 00:34:56,250
military grade, very illegal.

603
00:34:57,375 --> 00:35:01,833
And who was the one
who ordered you to scuttle the ship?

604
00:35:02,417 --> 00:35:03,958
Achilleo called him...

605
00:35:04,042 --> 00:35:06,000
Vasillias tou Enklimatos,

606
00:35:06,083 --> 00:35:07,292
the Kingpin...

607
00:35:08,042 --> 00:35:10,125
but we knew it was the Mayor.

608
00:35:11,333 --> 00:35:12,833
There was no customs check.

609
00:35:13,542 --> 00:35:17,125
We did not have to present
a bill of lading or manifest.

610
00:35:17,750 --> 00:35:20,375
We were never registered with Coast Guard,

611
00:35:20,458 --> 00:35:21,958
Homeland Security, none of it.

612
00:35:22,042 --> 00:35:24,333
I've been to many ports
all over this world.

613
00:35:25,333 --> 00:35:27,375
In order to make that happen...

614
00:35:28,500 --> 00:35:29,833
you have to own the city.

615
00:35:30,708 --> 00:35:32,458
Uh, "own the city" is correct?

616
00:35:33,375 --> 00:35:35,375
Yeah, in this case, it just might be.

617
00:35:37,167 --> 00:35:40,833
You said you were under orders
to scuttle the Northern Star

618
00:35:40,917 --> 00:35:42,250
if it was boarded.

619
00:35:43,875 --> 00:35:45,000
Who boarded the vessel?

620
00:35:45,833 --> 00:35:46,917
Coast Guard?

621
00:35:47,708 --> 00:35:49,542
Uh, no.

622
00:35:49,625 --> 00:35:50,625
One man.

623
00:35:52,500 --> 00:35:53,667
Daredevil.

624
00:35:58,083 --> 00:35:59,708
[Kirsten] The marshals are on their way.

625
00:35:59,792 --> 00:36:01,083
They'll keep you safe.

626
00:36:06,458 --> 00:36:08,875
[indistinct chatter]

627
00:36:08,958 --> 00:36:09,958
[Daniel] Hello.

628
00:36:10,458 --> 00:36:11,875
-[BB chuckles]
-Look at that.

629
00:36:11,958 --> 00:36:13,167
Ringside, baby.

630
00:36:13,708 --> 00:36:15,125
We're gonna be so close, you and me,

631
00:36:15,208 --> 00:36:16,708
that we're gonna be
covered in sweat tonight.

632
00:36:17,833 --> 00:36:20,333
That didn't come out
how it sounded in your head.

633
00:36:20,417 --> 00:36:23,500
Did not. You know what? I was saying it,
and I sort of realized

634
00:36:23,583 --> 00:36:26,167
as it was coming out that
it wasn't really what I meant.

635
00:36:26,250 --> 00:36:27,875
-So, uh...
-Mm.

636
00:36:27,958 --> 00:36:29,333
Anyways, um...

637
00:36:29,833 --> 00:36:31,500
thank you for inviting me.

638
00:36:32,500 --> 00:36:33,500
Of course.

639
00:36:33,583 --> 00:36:35,458
Yo! You're BB.

640
00:36:36,042 --> 00:36:37,375
Like The BB Report.

641
00:36:37,917 --> 00:36:39,458
Yeah, that... that's me. You watch that?

642
00:36:39,542 --> 00:36:40,750
Everybody watches it.

643
00:36:40,833 --> 00:36:42,375
My brother, my cousin, my tía.

644
00:36:42,458 --> 00:36:43,458
Yo, they're obsessed.

645
00:36:43,542 --> 00:36:44,875
[chuckles]

646
00:36:44,958 --> 00:36:47,000
Oh, can I get a pic?
It's gonna blow their mind.

647
00:36:47,083 --> 00:36:48,250
Yeah, for sure. Come on.

648
00:36:49,958 --> 00:36:51,125
[camera shutter clicks]

649
00:36:58,333 --> 00:36:59,708
Yo, appreciate you.

650
00:37:00,250 --> 00:37:01,500
My bad.

651
00:37:03,792 --> 00:37:05,333
[♪ tense music playing]

652
00:37:10,875 --> 00:37:13,125
Didn't realize
I was on a date with a celebrity.

653
00:37:13,792 --> 00:37:14,792
Come on.

654
00:37:16,000 --> 00:37:18,792
I'm not a celebrity and not a date.

655
00:37:20,042 --> 00:37:21,042
Yeah, not yet.

656
00:37:22,667 --> 00:37:24,333
[♪ "At A Disadvantage"
by Slick Naim playing]

657
00:37:27,292 --> 00:37:28,500
[siren blaring]

658
00:37:31,750 --> 00:37:32,750
[trainer] Make a fist.

659
00:37:33,625 --> 00:37:34,792
-Feel good?
-[Fisk] Yeah.

660
00:37:36,458 --> 00:37:37,708
Uh, that's not necessary.

661
00:37:37,792 --> 00:37:39,208
He'll never lay a glove on me.

662
00:37:39,292 --> 00:37:41,875
[trainer chuckles] I like
your style, Mayor.

663
00:37:44,708 --> 00:37:46,000
Anything?

664
00:37:46,083 --> 00:37:49,125
No. We have men on rooftops, subways,

665
00:37:49,208 --> 00:37:50,625
every entrance, and exit.

666
00:37:50,708 --> 00:37:53,500
Inside's covered, too.
We have Task Force in plainclothes

667
00:37:53,583 --> 00:37:55,583
and uniforms lugging serious firepower,

668
00:37:55,667 --> 00:37:56,833
so nothing's getting in.

669
00:37:57,542 --> 00:37:59,125
We'll need an entrance cleared.

670
00:38:01,333 --> 00:38:03,042
Preferably, the front doors.

671
00:38:05,375 --> 00:38:07,083
Sir, uh, I don't think tying yourself

672
00:38:07,167 --> 00:38:08,875
-to the stake is a very...
-[phone vibrating]

673
00:38:10,792 --> 00:38:12,000
...good idea.

674
00:38:13,417 --> 00:38:15,250
[Fisk] Looks like
you have somewhere to be.

675
00:38:19,667 --> 00:38:20,958
I'm not going anywhere...

676
00:38:21,458 --> 00:38:23,875
especially if you wanna
dangle yourself out as bait.

677
00:38:24,458 --> 00:38:25,833
Buck...

678
00:38:25,917 --> 00:38:26,917
go.

679
00:38:28,458 --> 00:38:30,292
We can't have any loose ends.

680
00:38:32,042 --> 00:38:33,250
[Buck sighs]

681
00:38:37,458 --> 00:38:38,500
[Fisk sighs]

682
00:38:38,583 --> 00:38:40,000
Don't worry, sir. Me and North got it.

683
00:38:40,958 --> 00:38:43,167
[rapper] ♪ I was working,
I couldn't understand it ♪

684
00:38:43,833 --> 00:38:46,208
♪ I was hurting, I was in a panic ♪

685
00:38:46,292 --> 00:38:48,667
♪ See, I felt like
I ain't meet the standards ♪

686
00:38:49,375 --> 00:38:51,125
♪ But yet, I made it at a disadvantage ♪

687
00:38:51,208 --> 00:38:52,208
[all cheering]

688
00:38:52,292 --> 00:38:54,208
♪ Yes, I made it at a disadvantage ♪

689
00:38:54,292 --> 00:38:57,417
♪ Yes, I made it at a disadvantage ♪

690
00:38:57,500 --> 00:38:59,292
♪ Yes, I made it at a disadvantage ♪

691
00:38:59,375 --> 00:39:01,625
-[Daniel] All right. I got prezzies.
-[BB] Ooh.

692
00:39:01,708 --> 00:39:03,750
I thought you're a foam finger kinda lady.

693
00:39:03,833 --> 00:39:04,958
[scoffs] I'm not.

694
00:39:05,042 --> 00:39:06,792
[Daniel] And there you go.

695
00:39:06,875 --> 00:39:08,167
Oh. Thank you.

696
00:39:08,250 --> 00:39:09,417
[Daniel] Look at this.

697
00:39:09,500 --> 00:39:10,833
Bobblehead Fisk, uh?

698
00:39:11,833 --> 00:39:13,542
-Very realistic.
-[Sheila chuckles]

699
00:39:13,625 --> 00:39:14,750
Look at that.

700
00:39:14,833 --> 00:39:16,417
Pure class.

701
00:39:17,083 --> 00:39:18,375
I hope you got the discount.

702
00:39:20,042 --> 00:39:21,333
There's a discount?

703
00:39:22,333 --> 00:39:23,333
Shit.

704
00:39:28,208 --> 00:39:30,375
Ladies and gentlemen,

705
00:39:30,458 --> 00:39:32,042
proud New Yorkers,

706
00:39:32,125 --> 00:39:35,000
welcome to Scrappin' In The Kitchen,

707
00:39:35,083 --> 00:39:40,583
benefiting the New York Born Again
revitalization project.

708
00:39:40,667 --> 00:39:43,833
The main event
will consist of three rounds.

709
00:39:43,917 --> 00:39:46,375
Winner determined by knockout,

710
00:39:46,458 --> 00:39:49,083
TKO, or points.

711
00:39:49,167 --> 00:39:51,583
Now, get out of your seats,

712
00:39:51,667 --> 00:39:55,167
clap your hands, and welcome--

713
00:39:55,250 --> 00:39:56,750
In purple trunks,

714
00:39:56,833 --> 00:39:59,625
weighing in at 235 pounds

715
00:39:59,708 --> 00:40:02,875
with a professional record
of thirty-two and two,

716
00:40:02,958 --> 00:40:06,667
-Mike "The Matterhorn" Melendez!
-[booing]

717
00:40:06,750 --> 00:40:10,292
And in the white corner,

718
00:40:10,375 --> 00:40:13,333
our hometown hero of Hell's Kitchen,

719
00:40:13,417 --> 00:40:15,042
wearing white trunks,

720
00:40:15,125 --> 00:40:18,167
weighing in at 325 pounds,

721
00:40:18,250 --> 00:40:21,125
with no professional boxing record,

722
00:40:21,208 --> 00:40:26,083
Mayor Wilson "Wildcard" Fisk!

723
00:40:26,167 --> 00:40:28,250
[all cheering]

724
00:40:28,333 --> 00:40:30,375
[♪ dramatic music playing]

725
00:40:30,833 --> 00:40:32,708
-[man 1] Yeah!
-[man 2] Boo!

726
00:40:32,792 --> 00:40:33,833
[all applauding]

727
00:40:54,875 --> 00:40:57,542
-[man 3] Boo!
-Yeah! [chanting] Fisk! Fisk! Fisk!

728
00:40:57,625 --> 00:40:59,708
Fisk! Fisk! Fisk! Fisk!

729
00:40:59,792 --> 00:41:01,125
Fisk!

730
00:41:14,375 --> 00:41:15,792
[referee] I want a clean fight.

731
00:41:15,875 --> 00:41:17,292
Nothing below the belt.

732
00:41:17,375 --> 00:41:19,667
Obey my commands.
Defend yourselves at all times.

733
00:41:19,750 --> 00:41:20,917
Touch gloves.

734
00:41:22,917 --> 00:41:24,292
[thuds]

735
00:41:28,458 --> 00:41:29,458
[all cheering]

736
00:41:30,667 --> 00:41:32,000
[man 4] Yeah!

737
00:41:34,458 --> 00:41:36,250
[♪ dramatic music continues]

738
00:41:54,000 --> 00:41:55,250
[bell dings]

739
00:41:55,333 --> 00:41:56,583
[Fisk breathing raggedly]

740
00:41:59,042 --> 00:42:00,792
-[Fisk grunts]
-[groans]

741
00:42:03,875 --> 00:42:07,000
[grunts, groans]

742
00:42:09,042 --> 00:42:10,500
Yeah! Yes!

743
00:42:10,583 --> 00:42:11,667
Let's go!

744
00:42:11,750 --> 00:42:13,875
That what you want? Fine!

745
00:42:13,958 --> 00:42:15,125
[Fisk yells]

746
00:42:22,000 --> 00:42:23,583
[tires screech]

747
00:42:28,792 --> 00:42:30,208
-[gunshots]
-[officers grunt]

748
00:42:30,917 --> 00:42:33,625
[both grunting]

749
00:42:38,708 --> 00:42:39,792
Hello, Mr. Savva.

750
00:42:43,500 --> 00:42:44,875
-[both grunting]
-[all cheering]

751
00:42:45,875 --> 00:42:47,042
[heavy breathing]

752
00:42:49,292 --> 00:42:50,958
[Fisk grunting]

753
00:42:52,042 --> 00:42:54,000
-[Mike groans]
-[bell dinging]

754
00:42:54,083 --> 00:42:56,458
[Fisk yelling]

755
00:42:56,542 --> 00:42:58,792
-Yeah! Yes! Yes!
-Oh, my God.

756
00:43:00,417 --> 00:43:02,083
[all cheering]

757
00:43:04,042 --> 00:43:06,083
[camera shutter clicking]

758
00:43:07,167 --> 00:43:09,250
[grunts, breathes heavily]

759
00:43:14,875 --> 00:43:16,792
Christofi's been taken care of.

760
00:43:17,750 --> 00:43:18,750
All right.

761
00:43:25,083 --> 00:43:27,667
-[breathes deeply]
-[bell dinging]

762
00:43:30,375 --> 00:43:32,208
[all cheering]

763
00:43:34,250 --> 00:43:36,292
[both grunting]

764
00:43:39,333 --> 00:43:40,792
[woman] Yeah!

765
00:43:40,875 --> 00:43:41,875
Yeah!

766
00:43:41,958 --> 00:43:44,167
[all cheering]

767
00:43:45,000 --> 00:43:46,625
[both grunting]

768
00:43:51,833 --> 00:43:54,042
[Fisk breathing heavily]

769
00:43:56,792 --> 00:43:58,500
[grunts softly]

770
00:43:58,583 --> 00:44:00,000
[straining]

771
00:44:03,458 --> 00:44:04,500
[Fisk breathing heavily]

772
00:44:05,000 --> 00:44:06,750
[Fisk grunts]

773
00:44:09,375 --> 00:44:11,917
[grunts, yells]

774
00:44:14,625 --> 00:44:16,542
[thuds]

775
00:44:17,583 --> 00:44:18,958
-[yells]
-[groans]

776
00:44:19,708 --> 00:44:21,375
[blood splattering]

777
00:44:27,500 --> 00:44:29,125
[woman screams] Oh!

778
00:44:29,208 --> 00:44:30,583
[people murmuring softly]

779
00:44:41,625 --> 00:44:43,167
[bell dinging]

780
00:44:49,792 --> 00:44:51,792
[all applauding, cheering]

781
00:45:03,625 --> 00:45:05,083
[bell dinging]

782
00:45:06,125 --> 00:45:07,583
[all cheering]

783
00:45:13,083 --> 00:45:14,083
Yeah!

784
00:45:14,167 --> 00:45:15,208
Oh, my God.

785
00:45:16,208 --> 00:45:19,250
-[camera shutter clicking]
-[cheering continues]

786
00:45:35,250 --> 00:45:36,625
You came.

787
00:45:37,417 --> 00:45:38,625
With a win.

788
00:45:39,500 --> 00:45:41,208
-I told you not to come.
-Kiss me.

789
00:45:41,292 --> 00:45:42,292
